  "decision_notes": "The problem requires a deep mathematical investigation into the optimality of the De Giorgi recurrence exponent in the context of 3D Navier-Stokes equations, specifically focusing on the sharpness of the 4/3 exponent and the impossibility of improving it via standard analytical routes.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "mathematical_investigator",
      "instructions": "Analyze the De Giorgi recurrence relation for the 3D Navier-Stokes equations to determine if the exponent beta = 4/3 is sharp. Specifically, investigate the construction of an extremizer (a solution or sequence of solutions) that saturates this bound. Evaluate the 8 standard analytical routes used to attempt improvements of this exponent and provide a rigorous justification for why each route is blocked or fails to yield a better exponent."
    },
    {
      "label": "logical_verifier",
      "instructions": "Review the findings regarding the 8 alternative routes and the extremizer construction. Verify that the conclusion regarding the sharpness of the 4/3 exponent is logically consistent with the failure of the alternative routes and the properties of the proposed extremizer."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "Combine the mathematical proof of the sharpness of the 4/3 exponent, the specific construction of the extremizer, and the detailed breakdown of why the 8 alternative routes are blocked into a single coherent response that answers the binary grading criteria."
}

